I don't know much about your engine, but I get a lot of them brought to me
sometime after they rebuild it, with low oil pressure. I find that at least
half of them have pinched oil cooler gaskets or something lodged in one of
the oil galleys.The third possibility is one of your oil pressure or relief
pistons being stuck in the bore. One thing you must do is to make sure those
valves slide up and down the bore easily and that there is no scratches in
the piston valve bore. I air hose out all of my blocks before I put them
back together.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT
71 Trike 1776cc 32/36 Progressive
VolksAir 1585cc 28 PICT
Ray, Kent WA
